title: ChebyshevInequality

! Chebyshev Inequality
$$
\Pr(\left|X-EX\right| > t) \leq \frac{\sigma^2}{t^2}
$$
If $$X_1,\ldots,X_n$$ is iid with finite mean and variance, and since $$Var(\hat{X}_n)=\sigma^2/n$$, then
$$
\Pr\left(\left|\hat{X}_n-EX\right| > t\right) \leq \frac{\sigma^2}{nt^2}
$$

